# Frontend rules

## Component organization

- **Pages** (`app/`): Thin route shells — fetch data, compose layout, delegate to components
- **Domain components** (`components/{domain}/`): Feature-specific UI (dashboard, transactions, accounts)
- **Shared UI** (`components/ui/`): shadcn/ui primitives — never put business logic here
- **Layout** (`components/layout/`): Shell, sidebar, nav, page headers
- **Forms** (`components/forms/`): Reusable form fields and form wrappers

### Size and composition

- Split components exceeding ~200 lines
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Extract hooks when logic is reused or a component handles both data and heavy UI
- One component per file; co-locate small sub-components only when truly private

## State management

- **Server state:** Fetch in pages or hooks; prefer server components where possible
- **Client state:** `store/` for global UI state (sidebar, filters, preferences)
- **Form state:** Local component state or react-hook-form — do not lift to global store
- **URL state:** Filters, pagination, and date ranges belong in search params when shareable

## API integration

- All HTTP calls go through `lib/api/` modules grouped by domain
- Never call `fetch` directly from components
- Types for API responses live in `types/` or alongside the API module
- Handle loading, empty, and error states explicitly in every data view

## Form handling

- Validation schemas in `lib/validations/` — shared between client preview and API shape
- Use react-hook-form + zod for interactive forms
- Optimize for keyboard: Tab order, Enter to submit, Escape to cancel
- Inline validation on blur; block submit until valid
- Transaction entry forms: amount → account → category → note (minimal fields first)

## Table patterns

- Consistent column alignment: text left, numbers right, dates center or left
- Sticky header on scrollable tables
- Row actions via icon buttons or right-click context — avoid action columns wider than needed
- Sortable columns where data is tabular; default sort by date descending for transactions
- Empty state with a clear call to action (e.g. "Add your first transaction")
- Pagination or virtual scroll for lists exceeding ~50 rows

## Dashboard consistency

- Page header: title, date range selector, primary action button
- Summary cards in a grid — 2–4 KPIs above the fold
- Charts below cards; tables below charts
- Use the same date range across all dashboard widgets on a page
- Loading skeletons matching final layout dimensions

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements keyboard reachable
- Visible focus rings (do not remove outline without replacement)
- Form inputs associated with labels (`htmlFor` / `aria-labelledby`)
- Icon-only buttons require `aria-label`
- Color is never the sole indicator of state — pair with text or icons
- Minimum contrast ratios per WCAG AA

## Styling

- shadcn/ui + Tailwind utilities only
- No deeply nested CSS or styled-components
- Use `cn()` for conditional classes
- Support dark mode via Tailwind `dark:` variants on all new components
